First Lady Michelle Obama announced that the International Franchise Association (IFA) has committed to hiring 80,000 veterans and military spouses by 2014. Additionally, the Military Spouse Employment Partnership (MSEP) has committed to employing 20,000 military spouses. These commitments, along with previous commitments from other organizations, represent a commitment to hire 100,000 veterans, wounded warriors, and military spouses by 2014. The First Lady also announced the Veterans Job Bank tool, an online resource that allows veterans and military spouses to search for job openings from committed employers. The U.S. Chamber of Commerce has supported the Joining Forces initiative by conducting hiring fairs for veterans and military spouses.